<TITLE>Mount Saint Nicholas</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ID="527.1" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is a peak in the remote southwestern section of Glacier National Park, in Montana, United States. 
<REF ID="527.2" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">It</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is a particularly steep, pointed rock pinnacle, and 
<REF ID="527.3" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Mount Saint Nicholas's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the peak's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 distinctive profile is visible from many summits in the southern half of the park. Because even 
<REF ID="527.4" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Mount Saint Nicholas's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the peak's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 easiest ascent route is technical, with poor rock quality, 
<REF ID="527.5" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is "considered the most dangerous and difficult mountain for climbers in Glacier National Park." (Edwards 1995:335)
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ID="527.6" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 excels in terms of steep vertical relief, even by the high standards prevalent in Glacier National Park. For example, 
<REF ID="527.7" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Mount Saint Nicholas's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the peak's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 northwest face rises one vertical mile (5,280 ft/1,609 m) in approximately 1.5 horizontal miles (7,920 ft/2.4 km). Due to 
<REF ID="527.8" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Mount Saint Nicholas's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the peak's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 pointed shape and isolation from the Continental Divide, 
<REF ID="527.9" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 has similarly precipitous drops in all directions.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
In 1926, Reverend Conrad Wellen, of Havre, Montana, made the first ascent of 
<REF ID="527.10" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
. This was a significant achievement, since 
<REF ID="527.11" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">that itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 had been considered by many to be unclimbable. (Edwards 1995:42) The standard route is the Northeast Ridge. Starting from the east side of 
<REF ID="527.12" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Mount Saint Nicholas itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">it itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the peak itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
, this route begins with a straightforward scramble up a gully to a prominent notch. From the notch a thousand vertical feet of somewhat technical climbing remain. (Edwards 1995:337)</PARAGRAPH>
</TEXT>
